                    Section 2 - Introduction to PyTorch
1 - Module Overview
Very brief run through of what the module will cover

2 - Prerequisites and Course Outline
There are some assumptions\prerequisites for taking the course
  - Some basic understanding of ML
    - Some other courses are recommended for students with no understanding of ML prior to taking the course
  - Comforatable programming in Python 3
  - Comfortable using Jupyter Notebooks
  - A basic understanding of Neural networks and how they work for deep learning
There is also a brief run through of the course curriculum
  - PyTorch is considered an alternative to Tensorflow

